U.K. Developer Candy Plans to Set Up Bank, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-10-16T08:23:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/u-k-developer-candy-plans-to-set-up-bank-telegraph-reports.html
U.K. property entrepreneur  Christian Candy , who with his brother Nick developed the One Hyde Park
project in London, plans to set up a 200 million-pound ($316
million) bridge-loan fund as a first step to creating a bank,
the Sunday Telegraph reported, citing Candy.  Candy may also discuss obtaining an additional 20 million
pounds of bridge financing from a London-based hedge fund, the
newspaper said, without disclosing where it got the information.  Details of the fund are due to be released shortly, the
Telegraph added. The fund, which will be offered to individuals
through CPC Groupâ€™s Omni Capital unit, is part of a move to
expand Omni into a financial services company that will include
insurance and banking, the newspaper said, citing Christian
